@page
@model IndexModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Know Your Sign";
}

<main>
    <section class="mb-3 d-flex justify-content-center mx-2 know">
        <div>
            <h1 class="text-center mt-5">Culio</h1>
            <p class="text-center">Enter Your month and day of birth to find out Your Zodiac Sign.</p>

            <div class="text-left">
                <form asp-action="Index" method="post">
                     <label for="day">Day:</label>
                    <div class="input-group">  
                        <input type="number" name="Day" id="day" class="form-control" min="1" max="31" placeholder="1">
                    </div>
                    <label for="month">Select Month:</label>

                    <select id="month" name="Month" class="form-select" aria-label="Default select example">
                        <option selected value="1">January</option>
                        <option value="2">February</option>
                        <option value="3">March</option>
                        <option value="4">April</option>
                        <option value="5">May</option>
                        <option value="6">June</option>
                        <option value="7">July</option>
                        <option value="8">August</option>
                        <option value="9">September</option>
                        <option value="10">October</option>
                        <option value="11">November</option>
                        <option value="12">December</option>
                    </select>

                    <div class="mt-2">
                        @* <button class="btn btn-secondary me-5 px-4" type="reset">Clear</button> *@
                        <button class="btn btn-primary px-4" type="submit">Find Sign</button>
                    </div>

                </form>
            </div>
            @if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(Model.Sign) && !string.IsNullOrEmpty(Model.Desc))
            {
                <div class="alert alert-info mt-4">
                    <h3>@Model.Sign</h3>
                    <p>@Model.Desc</p>
                </div>
            }

        </div>
    </section>
    <section class="container d-flex justify-content-center">
        <div class="mt-5 w-75">
            <h4>The History</h4>
            <p>
                Way back when, the Babylonians got super into astronomy and 
                basically sliced up the sun's path across the sky into 12 pieces, 
                each with its own cool constellation. The Greeks were all, "Whoa, 
                that's awesome!" and added their own mythological twist, turning 
                it into a cosmic personality test. Now, everyone's obsessed with 
                figuring out their sign and what it means for their love life, 
                career, and basically everything else. But here's the twist: these 
                signs aren't actually constellations, they're just 30-degree slices
                 of the sky, and thanks to Earth's wobbly dance, those slices have 
                 shifted around over time. So there you have it, the zodiac in a 
                 nutshell!
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>
</main>
